                        <interp inst="t18730922-name-272" type="surname" value="PERCY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18730922-name-272" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD PERCY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am manager to Mr. Lilley, who keeps a boot shop<lb></lb>on 28th August I saw the prisoner rise up from the doorway—I got up off my stool and missed a pair of boots worth 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—I went outside and saw the prisoner with a bag under his left arm—I asked him what he had got—he dropped the boots and ran away, and I pursued him, brought him back and gave him in custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I looked at the boots and felt them, but I never moved from the door.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">JOHN LORD</hi> (<hi rend="italic">City Policeman</hi> 874). I took the prisoner and found 8 1/2 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>. on him—Wheeler gave me the boots—the prisoner said at the station that he took them up and intended to buy them by paying 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. a week.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I did not intend to steal the boots. I should have paid him 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. down. I wanted them and was looking at them, but I never had them in my hand.</p>
